#### Ground truths

 346 video clips ranging from 5 to 15 seconds in duration is collected by 1080P/720P monocular cameras. The dataset contains approximately 82k frames and 2.2k unique pedestrian samples comprising a total of 337k bounding boxes, 3 type of people in the scenes: 

1. pedestrians: pedestrians with behaviour tags(precondition, crossing, attention/looking or not)
2. peds(bystanders): all other individual pedestrians in the scene.
3. people: groups of pedestrians, where individual people are hard to distinguish.

The dataset also provides demographic features,appearance(only in high-resolution video clips) for pedestrians, and context labels, driver reaction for vehicles.
